The paper deals with the optimization of vehicle scheduling and routing in an autonomous mobility-on-demand (AMoD) system, which involves the coordination of self-driving vehicles to transport customers within an urban environment. This topic is closely related to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for the optimization algorithms. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of mixed integer linear programming (MILP) for the optimization problem, which falls under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
